# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NAV-Erosion Screener — .gitignore
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Secrets / machine-specific (NEVER commit) ---
# NOTE: git does NOT support trailing inline comments — a "#" mid-line becomes
# part of the pattern. Keep every comment on its own line.
# CLAUDE.local.md: your local paths + where the FMP key lives
CLAUDE.local.md
# .env: dotenv holding the FMP_API_KEY
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*_secret*
*apikey*

# --- Python ---
.venv/
venv/
env/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- IDE ---
# .idea/: PyCharm
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml

# --- OS cruft ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Project data & outputs
# Everything below is regeneratable via fetch_data.py / build_board.py,
# so it's ignored by default — EXCEPT the two sample funds, kept so the
# repo runs out-of-the-box without an API key.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Ignore all cached fund data...
data/*.csv
data/*.json

# ...but keep the TSLY + NVDY samples so the project is demoable as-is.
!data/TSLY_prices.csv
!data/TSLY_dividends.csv
!data/NVDY_prices.csv
!data/NVDY_dividends.csv

# Dated ranked boards (regenerated each run)
ranked_board_*.json

# Generated artifacts: charts, PDFs, HTML reports, viz data
# Ignore the contents but keep the folder itself (via .gitkeep).
output/*
!output/.gitkeep
*.png
*.pdf
viz_data.json

# Keep committed docs that happen to be PDFs? If you want the investor
# guide tracked, un-ignore it explicitly:
# !NAV_Erosion_Model_Explained.pdf